<NetworkConfiguration xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/ServiceHosting/2011/07/NetworkConfiguration">
  <VirtualNetworkConfiguration>
    <Dns />
    <LocalNetworkSites>
      <LocalNetworkSite name="localNetworkSiteName">
        <AddressSpace>
          <AddressPrefix>10.1.0.0/16</AddressPrefix>
        </AddressSpace>
        <VPNGatewayAddress>1.1.1.1</VPNGatewayAddress>
      </LocalNetworkSite>
    </LocalNetworkSites>
    <VirtualNetworkSites>
      <VirtualNetworkSite name="virtualNetworkSiteName" AffinityGroup="affinityGroupName">
        <AddressSpace>
          <AddressPrefix>192.168.100.0/24</AddressPrefix>
        </AddressSpace>
        <Subnets>
          <Subnet name="frontendsubnet">
            <AddressPrefix>192.168.100.0/28</AddressPrefix>
          </Subnet>
          <Subnet name="backendsubnet">
            <AddressPrefix>192.168.100.32/28</AddressPrefix>
          </Subnet>
          <Subnet name="gatewaysubnet">
            <AddressPrefix>192.168.100.48/28</AddressPrefix>
          </Subnet>
        </Subnets>
        <Gateway>
          <VPNClientAddressPool>
            <AddressPrefix>192.168.101.0/24</AddressPrefix>
          </VPNClientAddressPool>
          <ConnectionsToLocalNetwork>
            <LocalNetworkSiteRef name="localNetworkSiteName">
              <Connection type="IPsec" />
            </LocalNetworkSiteRef>
          </ConnectionsToLocalNetwork>
        </Gateway>
      </VirtualNetworkSite>
    </VirtualNetworkSites>
  </VirtualNetworkConfiguration>
</NetworkConfiguration>

<NetworkConfiguration xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/ServiceHosting/2011/07/NetworkConfiguration" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <VirtualNetworkConfiguration>
    <Dns>
      <DnsServers />
    </Dns>
    <LocalNetworkSites>
      <LocalNetworkSite name="localNetworkSiteName">
        <AddressSpace>
          <!-- A customer can define multiple address prefixes in this section. -->
          <AddressPrefix>10.1.0.0/16</AddressPrefix>
        </AddressSpace>
        <!-- VPNGatewayAddress specifies the public IP address of the customer VPN gateway device. -->
        <VPNGatewayAddress>1.1.1.1</VPNGatewayAddress>
      </LocalNetworkSite>
    </LocalNetworkSites>
    <VirtualNetworkSites>
      <VirtualNetworkSite name="virtualNetworkSiteName" Location="North Central US">
        <AddressSpace>
          <!-- A customer can define multiple address prefixes in this section. -->
          <AddressPrefix>192.168.0.0/24</AddressPrefix>
        </AddressSpace>
        <Subnets>
          <Subnet name="SubnetName">
            <AddressPrefix>192.168.0.0/28</AddressPrefix>
          </Subnet>
        </Subnets>
        <DnsServersRef />
      </VirtualNetworkSite>
    </VirtualNetworkSites>
  </VirtualNetworkConfiguration>
</NetworkConfiguration>
